<mark>HTML (HyperText Markup Language)</mark> is the standard, foundational <b>markup language</b> used to create and structure web pages, describing their layout through elements and tags (e.g., headings, paragraphs, images).<br>It acts as the skeleton for web content, allowing browsers to interpret and display text, <del>Objects</del> <ins>images,</ins> and other multimedia.
<hr>
<em><strong>Cascading Style Sheets (CSS)</strong> <small> is a <b>style sheet language</b> used for specifying the presentation and styling of a document written in a <strike>markup language,</strike> such as HTML or XML (including XML dialects such as SVG, MathML, or XHTML).<br>CSS is a cornerstone technology of the World Wide Web, alongside &nbsp; HTML and JavaScript<small></em>
